article.headline: Princeton 60, Harvard 51
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Judson Wallace scored 12 points and grabbed 16 rebounds Friday to lead Princeton to a 60-51 win over Harvard. The victory clinches at least a tie for the championship in the Ivy league. Scott Greeman scored 14 points and Will Venable added 12 as the Tigers (18-7, 11-1 Ivy) won their seventh consecutive game and 12th in their last 13. Kevin Rogus scored 15 points and Jason Norman added eight points and six rebounds for Harvard (4-22, 3-10). The Tigers led 26-20 at halftime. Harvard went on a 16-5 run four minutes into the second half to take a 44-41 lead on a Luke McCrone jump shot with 12:04 left in the game. But the Tigers held the Crimson to one field goal the rest of the way to clinch their ninth Ivy League title in the last 16 years.
